---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../utils/seo';

const crumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Terms of Use', href: '/terms' },
];

const effectiveDate = 'January 1, 2025';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The terms governing your use of theherbertteam.com, including content disclaimers, lending disclosures, and limitations of liability."
  heroEyebrow="Legal"
  heroTitle="Terms of Use"
  heroSubtitle={`Effective ${effectiveDate}. By using this website you agree to the terms below.`}
  heroImage="/images/hero/contact-hero.jpg"
  heroImageAlt=""
  crumbs={crumbs}
  showHeroCtas={false}
  heroSize="sm"
  schema={breadcrumbSchema(crumbs)}
>
  <Section bg="white">
    <div class="prose mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="lead">
        This website is operated by {site.advisor}, {site.nmls}, a licensed mortgage advisor originating through{' '}
        {site.institution}, {site.institutionNmls}. By accessing or using this site, you agree to these Terms of Use. If
        you do not agree, please do not use the site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Informational Purpose Only</h2>
      <p>
        The content on this website is provided for general educational and informational purposes. It is marketing
        material, not financial, legal, tax, or investment advice. Mortgage guidelines, program parameters, and market
        conditions change frequently, and general information cannot account for your specific circumstances. Consult
        your own attorney, CPA, or financial advisor before making decisions with legal or tax consequences.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Not a Commitment to Lend</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on this website constitutes an offer or commitment to lend, an offer to enter into an interest rate lock
        agreement, or a guarantee of loan approval. All loans are subject to credit approval, income and asset
        verification, satisfactory property appraisal, title review, and program eligibility. Not all applicants will
        qualify.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Rates, Payments, and Examples</h2>
      <p>
        Any rate, payment, fee, or scenario shown on this site — including calculator output, worked examples, and
        program comparison figures — is illustrative and for education only. Actual terms depend on your credit profile,
        loan amount, property type, occupancy, loan-to-value ratio, debt-to-income ratio, lock period, and market
        conditions at the time of application. Rates and terms are subject to change without notice.
      </p>
      <p>
        The mortgage calculator on this site produces estimates. Property taxes, homeowners insurance, mortgage
        insurance, and HOA dues vary substantially by property and are not quoted here. Only a Loan Estimate issued
        after a complete application reflects actual figures.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Program Availability</h2>
      <p>
        Loan programs described on this site vary by state, property type, occupancy, and borrower eligibility. Programs
        may be modified, restricted, or discontinued at any time without notice. Descriptions of guidelines are general
        summaries and are not underwriting decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Testimonials and Reviews</h2>
      <p>
        Testimonials and reviews appearing on this site reflect the individual experiences of clients who have used our
        services. They are individual results, and results vary. We do not claim they are typical, and they are not a
        guarantee or prediction of future outcomes. Reviews displayed through the embedded Google Reviews widget are
        sourced from Google and are not edited by us.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Third-Party Links and Embedded Services</h2>
      <p>
        This site links to and embeds third-party services, including the Primis Bank application portal, Pivot Point
        CRM forms, a Google Reviews widget, and Google Maps. We do not control those services and are not responsible
        for their content, availability, security, or privacy practices. Your use of a third-party service is governed
        by that provider&rsquo;s terms and privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Electronic Communications and Consent</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit a form or provide your phone number, you consent to receive communications from us by email,
        phone, and text message, including by automated means, regarding your inquiry. Consent is not a condition of
        obtaining any loan or service. Message and data rates may apply. You may opt out at any time by replying STOP to
        a text, using the unsubscribe link in an email, or calling <a href={site.phoneHref}>{site.phone}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Accuracy of Information You Provide</h2>
      <p>
        You agree that any information you submit is accurate and that you are authorized to provide it. Submitting
        false information in connection with a mortgage application may constitute mortgage fraud, a federal crime.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the site for any unlawful purpose or in violation of these terms</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the site or its underlying systems</li>
        <li>Introduce malware, scrape content at scale, or interfere with the site&rsquo;s operation</li>
        <li>Reproduce, republish, or distribute site content commercially without written permission</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on this site — text, graphics, logos, layout, and code — is owned by {site.name} or its licensors and
        is protected by copyright and trademark law. You may view and print content for personal, non-commercial use.
        All other use requires prior written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        This site is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available,&rdquo; without warranties of any kind, express
        or implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy, or
        non-infringement. We do not warrant that the site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful
        components.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, {site.name}, {site.advisor}, and {site.institution} are not liable for any
        indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages arising from your use of this site or reliance
        on its content, including lost profits or lost opportunities, even if advised of the possibility of such
        damages.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Fair Lending</h2>
      <p>
        We do business in accordance with the Federal Fair Housing Law and the Equal Credit Opportunity Act. It is
        illegal to discriminate against any person because of race, color, religion, sex, handicap, familial status,
        national origin, or because all or part of the applicant&rsquo;s income derives from a public assistance program.
        Equal Housing Lender.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict of law rules. Any
        dispute arising from these terms or your use of the site will be brought in the state or federal courts located
        in Williamson County, Texas.
      </p>

      <h2>15. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise these terms at any time. The effective date above reflects the current version, and continued use
        of the site after changes are posted constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>16. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        {site.advisor} &middot; {site.name}<br />
        {site.address}<br />
        <a href={site.phoneHref}>{site.phone}</a><br />
        <a href={site.emailHref}>{site.email}</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Full licensing detail and state license numbers are on the <a href="/licensing">Licensing &amp; Disclosures</a> page.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm">
        {site.advisor} | {site.nmls} | {site.institution} | {site.institutionNmls} · Equal Housing Lender · Member FDIC
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</PageLayout>
